It signifies releaselocation. E = Europe, U = the US, J = Japan. Some other variations for Korea, Germany, China, France, Spain is also sometimes occuring.

@tbb-monger
The european ones are always in at least english, but often french, german, and such as well. Those without english are normally labeled (F) for french and such.
